<br>
There were few comedic lines, but they really stood out to me. Of course all of it seemed to come from Gimli. I think it could have done away from the lame jokes. SW-EP2 and C3PO is a perfect example. Nothing, in that film, pissed me off more in than those moronic one liners (well maybe Hayden Christensen's inability to act). Gimli's one liners were no where near as bad, but it immediately made me think back to SW-EP2 and brought up those feelings of disgust.<br>
<br>
Overall, I loved the movie. I really liked the on screen version of Gollum and they did well portraying his internal conflicts with himself. The Ents were amazing, although Perry and Pippin's time with Treebeard were quite shortened for the film. Legolas and Aragorn still kick some ass, and Eowyn is absolutely beautiful. <br>
<br>
One shock I did find was that the ending of the movie wasnt what I had expected. The book went on a little further and at the end of the movie, Gollum has a dialogue with himself that forshadows what is to come. I think they could have gone with the book ending, but then again it would have been one hell of a cliffhanger and this leaves one interesting possibility of an opening scene for Return of the King. <br>
<br>
I will definitely go and see it again this weekend to pick up anything I missed. Overall, a great film.  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Overlord of Darkwind</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=527339" target="top">Magelo Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xendrix>Xendrix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/20/02 11:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1703.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I just saw LOTR The Two Towers</span><hr size=1> I saw it and loved it.  I went into it knowing the story would stray a bit from the book version, so I had an open mind about it.  The strayings and things they left out are what most people are disappointed with.  Also, the portrayal of Faramir was an unnecessary change from the book that many do not like.<br>
<br>
Having said that, if you go watch it as a new movie and not expect a very close following of the book, most will enjoy it quite a bit.  I will go and see it again in the theatre myself.  After all, my wife forgot to use my free pass that came with the extended DVD version, and the pass expires at the end of the year.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
