<br>
All I got to say is, they better have Gandolf/Samuran in Isengard. I can live with the changes although the one with Farimir doesn't ADD to the story and it takes longer to add in. I understand they have to edit and add certain things so the audience can follow the Author's intent (like the &quot;possession&quot; of the king so the audience can quickly realize that Samuran is behind his decisions). But to add something in the movie that is a distraction when they could have used THAT time to include some of the other things. <br>
<br>
Also, Fellowship excluded alot of material (like Tom Bombadil and that 17 years passed from when Bilbo left the Shire and when Frodo departed toward Mordor - among other things.) But I definately agree that SOME things have to be retained and some things shouldn't be altered.<br>
<br>
But I give the film big Kudo's to getting the landscape right - JRR Tolkein spent alot of time describing the surrounding scenery. Everything was certainly BIG.<br>
